The '''1984 Tbilisi gas explosion''' was a [[gas explosion]] in a nine-storey apartment block in [[Tbilisi]], [[Georgia_(country)|Georgia]] on 2 December 1984 that killed at least 100 people.<ref>{{cite book|last=Oberg|first=James E.|title=Uncovering Soviet disasters: exploring the limits of glasnost|publisher=Random House|date=February 1988|pages=110|isbn=978-0-394-56095-3}}</ref>
