'''Ash Kalra''' is an [[United States|American]] [[politician]] serving in the [[California State Assembly]]. He is a [[California Democratic Party|Democrat]] representing the [[California's 27th State Assembly district|27th Assembly District]], encompassing parts of eastern [[San Jose, California|San Jose]].

Kalra was first elected to the Assembly after defeating fellow [[California Democratic Party|Democrat]] [[Madison Nguyen]] in 2016. Prior to being elected to the Assembly, he was a member of the [[San Jose City Council]] where he represented District 2 in South San Jose for eight years.

Kalra is the first [[Indian-American]] to serve in the [[California State Legislature]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Day One for New Assemblymember Ash Kalra|url=https://a27.asmdc.org/video/day-one-new-assemblymember-ash-kalra|website=California State Assembly|accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref>

In 2011, Kalra was arrested and sentenced to serve in a jail work-detail program and undergo counseling after pleading guilty to misdemeanor [[drunk driving]]. <ref>{{cite web|title=San Jose Councilman Ash Kalra sentenced for DUI|url=https://www.sfgate.com/crime/article/San-Jose-Councilman-Ash-Kalra-sentenced-for-DUI-2366120.php|website=San Francisco Gate|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref>

