{{italic title}}
[[Image:Adrienne lecouvreur dans cornlie.jpg|left|thumb|[[Adrienne Lecouvreur]], as Cornelia in ''The Death of Pompey'']]
[[Image:Corneille La mort de Pompée Paris Sommaville Courbé 1644.jpg|thumb|First publication of ''The Death of Pompey'']]

'''''The Death of Pompey''''' (''La Mort de Pompée'') is a tragedy by the French playwright [[Pierre Corneille]] on the death of [[Pompey|Pompey the Great]]. It was first performed in 1642, with [[Julius Caesar]] played by [[Molière]].  Like many of Corneille's plays, it is noted for the high tones of its heroine, [[Cornelia Metella|Cornelia]], who admits that her enemy is noble and generous but warns him when he releases her that she will continue to seek his death.<ref>[[Louis Auchincloss]], ''False Dawn'' p 4 {{ISBN|0-385-18021-7}}</ref>

